ibis.cashmere.constellation

Interface LaunchFunction

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface LaunchFunction
    Represents a method to launch a library function LibFunc. The supplied parameters can be used to enqueue the library function.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void launch(org.jocl.cl_command_queue queue, int num_events_in_wait_list, org.jocl.cl_event[] events_in_wait_list, org.jocl.cl_event event)
      Launches a library function.

    • Method Detail

      • launch

        void launch(org.jocl.cl_command_queue queue,
            int num_events_in_wait_list,
            org.jocl.cl_event[] events_in_wait_list,
            org.jocl.cl_event event)
     throws org.jocl.CLException
        Launches a library function. This means that the queue should be used to enqueue the library function. The parameter events_in_wait_list will contain num_events_in_wait_list events that should finish before the library function can be executed. In event the library function should return the event on which other OpenCL commands should wait.
        Parameters:
        queue - the cl_command_queue with which library function executions can be enqueued
        num_events_in_wait_list - the number of events in events_in_wait_list
        events_in_wait_list - contains num_events_in_wait_list events that should finish before the library function
        event - the cl_event that should be returned by this execution of the library function
        Throws:
        org.jocl.CLException - if an error occurs within the OpenCL library.
